<p>Hi all, I’m a lvl 50 pally now thx for giving me those suggestion in a earlier post they really helped, well I challenged my friend to a duel he is a lvl 50 necro this was back went I was a 46 pally I basically got my butt handed to me, he dot'ed me and slowed me (I had my magic resist up at 104 I could n't resist nothing launched on me) I could n't even get a hit in and every time I got close he would run or use shadowstep and I'd lose track of him, I tried chain stunning (i.e. cease, desist, stun) did n't work he resisted most of them except stun he resisted even root and even flash of light in a attempt to blind him(he told me he had his magic resist at 100). Now I’m a lvl 50 pally he's a 52 necro I planned to challenge him for a rematch any suggestions on strategies I should use or what resistances I should get up or anything that might help me or should I wait for a later lvl to duel him. We had some terms in our duel that we can only use self buffs this time I got the Jboots to increase my movement speed I plan to use that to get him into close combat... If you guys can give me any suggestions on how I should approach this it would be a great help. sry my post is a bit long I wanted to get as much information in as I can. Also i almost forgot i made him lom nearing the end of the duel since he changed into his skelly form it was n't him that killed me it was his dot's.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />FFXI- <br />Luidian (elvaan) - Bismarck <br />54-thf, 37-rng, 27-war, 25-nin, 23-sam, 20-whm, 7-rdm <br />LS - Secta Victoriae <br />--------------------------------- <br /></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >2 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
