		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=285878"><span class="Guru">Steinhound</span></a><b><span class="Guru"><br/>Guru</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />346 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=6;mid=1090997271467202033;page=1;howmany=50#1091018363479804007"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Hello Warrioroflight; <br /> <br />Dueling has many role playing aspects and therefore luck play a huge part in any duel with two close level characters (exluding the obvious). <br /> <br />As in any Duel, any PvP player will tell you resists are very primal needs to increase your chances. Although the Necro you duelled only had 100 SvM the spells you used (cease, desist, stun and Flash of light are all early level and any 50 will more then likely resist them, they are not like NPC's who do not have as high MR as PC's. The spells the necro would used would have been of much higher level. However and more importantly, it is not just your SvM you need when you fight a necro, Most of there spells are disease and poison based, this is where i think the duel has swung in the necro's favour. You need to increase on those as high as you can, using your own if not a clerics buffs to help. <br /> <br />Pallies at later levels (mainly the sixties) are much more powerful duellers, the resists are much higher and detrimental casters are at a disadvantage to Benefical casters such as a pally. SK's and Necros need to heal themselves by drawing your life and you can resist it, your benefical heal are never resisted. Also they like the fear spells, Pallies become completely immune to fear with AA advancement. <br /> <br />Load your higher level stuns and your heal over time spells, don't always count on your LoH it won't always be up. Shackle of tunare is a duel winner but again it is purely down to luck if it lands. But that is a 65 spell, instill is still good but better to cast on the pets of caster rather then the caster themselves. <br /> <br />Keep your far plane clip up if your against shadow steppers and use your bow, it will sometimes face you in the direction of the caster, or a stun then just look for the beam of light. <br /> <br />There are many other spells as you advanve that will give you the edge as resists come more and more into play. On venril sathir in the arena event, the pallies and rogues came out top. <br />Rogues because they hid from a duel then backstabbed the winner ( bloody cowards). <br /> <br />Also a faster weapon like the WMBS or Vitality + Shield  will help. Fast damage. Even bow the caster when you get the better bows just to annoy him if he keeps running about. <br /> <br />After all this is said, your main thing is poison and desease resists, even then Luck plays a HUGE part. <br /> <br />Good luck hope it helps.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />'The only thing I cannot resist is temptation.', Oscar Wilde. </td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
