		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=6;mid=1090997271467202033;page=1;howmany=50#109120475973340782"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Necro's can be tough, due to their large array of dots.  Unfortunately, MR may not help you, because many of their dots are disease and poison based.  Since you dont have fear, you will have to ROOT THE PET.  I would alternately be casting stun and dispel magic also (sometimes casting dispel on your self). <br /> <br />Their is a bow that proc's stun also, I think its a 'sturdy bow', but I'm to lazy to look it up.  Also, if you have a high level friend that has a ton of leadership points, you might want to group with him and one other to get extra attack buffs that cannot be dispelled (hehe).  What you really need out that is spell awareness, so you can time your stuns for when you really need it. <br /> <br />Once you get your necro dueler in melee range, BASH STUN BASH.  If you kill the necro, the pet will fall soon after (just run around and he will dispel).  Blind can be your good friend also, as he may not have his spell gems memorized.  I would also have a clicky root available (drops in everfrost off of a goblin jailer I think). <br /> <br />If you have any clicky items (like jboots), I would have those buffs up before I got temp and kei, because you can refresh a clicky buff every time the necro tries to dispel magic on you (another good reason for having spell awareness). <br /> <br />Please note, spamming jboots can sometimes break root.  Have it hotkey'd. <br /> <br />Watch out for gate!  A lot of times a necro will bind himself in a safe spot in the same zone and gate to throw you off.  Same with shadowstep.  This will be your biggest pain in an outdoor duel.  In an arena duel, not so much a problem. <br /> <br />If in an outdoor duel, the necro might also do an FD/Train if he can gate on you. <br /> <br />I dont think using self buffs is a fair for you.  Reason being is that if you die to his dots, you will lose exp (in an arena duel).  Since you do not have dots, when the necro dies, nothing happens. <br /> <br />Another cute tactic (hehe).  Duel a friend in the same zone (safe place) and let him kill you.  Go back and loot all your stuff except maybe one insignificant item and then have a high level cleric rez you.  DO NOT ACCEPT THE REZ, but keep the rez box up in a corner somewhere.  If things go to crap, you can accept the rez and essentially GATE to your safe spot without losing the duel.  Yeah, you will have rez effects, but it will buy you some time. <br /> <br />I would ask some of ur pally buddies for a good spell line up. <br /> <br />PvP is all about outsmarting your opponent as some classes have a definative advantage in PvP (Bard's, SK's, Druid's, Necro's). <br />Some of this may be applicable, some may not.  I have just made you aware of some options that you have never considered.  Additionally, you will find yourself in many situations in which you are not doing a FRIENDLY duel.  In this case, I make sure I'm the winner. <br /> <br />Peace...</p>
